<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-12-07T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-12-07T02:00:00-05:00" n="497" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10649: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-07T15:00:00+08:00">December 7, 1929—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received December 7—10:35 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1101. Following from American Consul General at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“December 5, noon. At a point between Ichang and Itu all shipping
                                    is being heavily fired upon by troops ashore. British ship <hi rend="italic">Wanhsien</hi>, escorted by British naval
                                    vessel, was heavily fired on yesterday near Itu, and latter
                                    returned the fire with effectiveness. American ships will be
                                    escorted through danger zone by U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Guam</hi>, now at Ichang.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>